[0.024, "o", "This is a SQL query that references **anonymized PII tokens** produced by the `anon` tool in this repo.\r\n\r\nThe original query likely looked something like:\r\n\r\n```sql\r\nSELECT * FROM crew WHERE email = 'jean.dupont@example-air.com' AND phone = '+33 6 12 34 56 78';\r\n```\r\n\r\nAfter running through `anon`, the real email and phone number were replaced with deterministic placeholder tokens:\r\n\r\n- `jean.dupont@example-air.com` — the first unique email address encountered in the input\r\n- `+33 6 12 34 56 78` — the first unique French phone number encountered\r\n\r\nThe query itself just selects all columns from a `crew` table where both the email and phone match specific values. The anonymized version preserves the SQL structure so you can still debug/analyze the query logic without exposing real personal data.\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "Restored 2 entities\r\n"]
